description:
A Skylit Drive is an American post-hardcore band from Lodi, California. The band has released one DVD, one EP and four studio albums: Wires...and the Concept of Breathing (2008), Adelphia (2009), Identity On Fire (2011) and recently Rise (2013). The band consists of Michael Jagmin (lead vocals), Nick Miller (lead guitar), Michael Labelle (rhythm guitar, unclean vocals), Kyle Simmons (bass, keyboards) and Brandon Richter (drums). Original member Joey Wilson left the band in 2012, reducing the band to a five-piece.[1] In 2014, Brian White and Cory La Quay departed from the band, and were later replaced by Michael Labelle and Brandon Richter. The band has toured internationally both as headliner and support-act.
